step_data.thought:
I see that my attempt to click the 'Reorder' button with bid '741' resulted in a timeout error. Looking at the current page, I notice that I'm now on a 'New Order' page in the Magento Admin Panel. It seems that the system has already started the reorder process for the canceled order #000000074, as I can see the items from that order listed in the 'Items Ordered' section.

The page shows two items:
1. Daria Bikram Pant (SKU: WP10-29-Black) - USD 51.00
2. Sprite Yoga Strap 8 foot (SKU: 24-WG086) - USD 17.00

These items are already added to the new order with quantities of 1 each. The subtotal is USD 68.00, with shipping handling of USD 10.00, making the grand total USD 78.00.

Since the items are already added to the new order, my goal of reordering the items from the canceled order has essentially been accomplished. The system has automatically created a new order with the same items. To complete the reorder process, I should submit this order by clicking the 'Submit Order' button.
